From: Assistant <assistant@local>
Date: Fri May 8 2026
Subject: [PATCH] libbb: Fix sha1_end shaNI reference on non-x86 architectures

Busybox 1.37.0's sha1_end() references sha1_process_block64_shaNI under
#if ENABLE_SHA1_HWACCEL, but the function is only declared when
__x86_64__ or __i386__ is defined.  This causes build failures when
cross-compiling for non-x86 targets with a defconfig generated on x86.

Add the missing architecture guard.
---
 libbb/hash_md5_sha.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/libbb/hash_md5_sha.c b/libbb/hash_md5_sha.c
index abc123..def456 100644
--- a/libbb/hash_md5_sha.c
+++ b/libbb/hash_md5_sha.c
@@ -1313,8 +1313,10 @@ unsigned FAST_FUNC sha1_end(sha1_ctx_t *ctx, void *resbuf)
 
 	hash_size = 8;
 	if (ctx->process_block == sha1_process_block64
 #if ENABLE_SHA1_HWACCEL
+# if defined(__GNUC__) && (defined(__i386__) || defined(__x86_64__))
 	 || ctx->process_block == sha1_process_block64_shaNI
+# endif
 #endif
 	) {
 		hash_size = 5;
